{
  "$comment": "Claude Code settings for the Linus repo. PostToolUse hooks run ruff format/isort/ruff-check on Python edits and prettier --write on Markdown edits. Permissions allowlist mirrors the 'Allowlist (auto-execute OK)' section of CLAUDE.md. Key additions vs prior version: read-only git commands (status/log/diff/branch/show/rev-parse/reflog/for-each-ref/cherry-pick), git worktree management, gh read commands, python/ruff/pytest execution, standard file-read ops (ls/cat/head/tail/wc/find/grep/awk/sed/sort/uniq/xargs), and compound shell constructs (for-loops, while-loops, python3 heredocs). Compound constructs are allowlisted here but remain subject to the CLAUDE.md policy: the compound is allowed iff every command and side-effect inside it is allowlisted — pattern matching cannot enforce this, it is a judgment call at execution. Forbidden ops (git push --force, git reset --hard, git rebase, rm -rf outside /tmp, sudo, curl, pip install, brew install) remain under Require confirmation. mdlint is deliberately NOT in the hook chain — mdlint 0.3.15 silently auto-fixes MD004 even without --fix, which corrupts in-prose '+' characters. See CLAUDE.md Known Library Quirks.",
  "permissions": {
    "allow": [
